LAFIA- United Women For Peace Initiative (UWPI), a Non- Governmental (NGO), Organization on Monday distributed food items worth thousands of naira to over 50 women in the state, in her bid to ensure that women in Nasarawa state do not experience any lack during the festive season. Items distributed include: Maggi, red oil, groundnut oil, salt, spaghetti, semovita, and others. National Coordinator of the NGO, Hon. Aisha Abubakar, who distributed the food items in Lafia, explained that they saw the need to distribute the food items to women, especially Widows who do not have what to eat during the festive season. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! According to her, “We founded this NGO to be able to reach out to women and help them achieve their dreams and aspirations, through counseling, financial support and any other way we can be of help to them.” “This is not the first time we are distributing food items to women in the state. We did it last year and we hoping to continue this way by showing love to as many women as possible. So we need help from the government and other good spirited individuals in order for us to continue touching lives positively”, she said. PDP Group Berates Adeleke Over Issue Unknown To Him Lawmaker Distributes Food Items To Over 3000 Constituents, Fetes Children For Christmas Also Speaking at the event tagged, “The Bedrock For Women Empowerment”, Hon Tessy Nneli, State Coordinator of the UWPI said that the aim of NGO was to make sure that women are brought together to know the importance of peace in the home and society at large, noting that, “Without peace, there can’t be any meaningful development anywhere in the world. “We encourage the women to make sure they obey their husbands. Our coming together is to see that women behave well. We kick against women leaving their husbands to other men. Today we are here to give food items to some of the women.” “We don’t have people who are funding us, we are doing it on our own. The National Coordinator made the provision for today’s program. She has been very supportive and we are very grateful to her.” “By this time last year, we were at the Dalhatu Araf Specialist Hospital (DASH) to make donation to sick people. The program has been on for about five years now. We are fully registered with the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC) and recognized by the Ministry of Women Affairs both at the Federal and State levels”, Hon Tessy said. One of the beneficiaries, Mrs. Maryam Adamu expressed gratitude to the NGO for the food items, noting that, ” It will go a long way to cushion the hardship which most women are currently experiencing in the state due to several restrictions imposed by the government in order to tackle the Coronavirus pandemic. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION